A Service is use to connect the user with the applications deployed in the pod.


User Accessing the application from the host server.
Eg:
User system: 192.12.0.1
Node: 192.12.0.10
Pod: 10.123.1.1

IP's are in differnt network to connect it.

Service is use to interact between the user and the web app in the pod network.

Types of service:
Node Port
Cluster IP
Load Balancer

Node Port:
target Port 80 will be from Pod
Port 80 will be from service
port 30008 will be from Node (between 30000-32500)
If the user do a curl http://192.12.0.10:30008 (application can be accessed)

Service can be used:
Single Pod on a Single Node (curl http://192.12.0.10:30008)
Multiple Pods on a Single Node (curl http://192.12.0.10:30008)
Multiple Pods on a Multiple Nodes (curl http://192.12.0.1:30008, curl http://192.12.0.2:30008, curl http://192.12.0.3:30008)



Service need to connect with pod (selector & label)
Service need to connedct with target port of pod (80, service port 80, nodeport 30008)

service.yml
apiVersion: v1
kind: Service
metadata:
  name: myapp-service
spec:
    type: NodePort
    ports:
     - targetport: 80
       port: 80
       nodeport: 30008
    selector:
      name: myapp
      type: front-end



